{
  "text": "The third conservation score considered is an information-theoretic approach based on the JSD [CITATION_1] . The JSD is a common method used to compare probability distributions. In this application, the first distribution is based on the amino acid distribution in column i, and the second distribution is based on a background distribution (calculated from the BLOSUM62 alignments). The JSD is calculated by:",
